========,1,preface.
Little Rock Township is a township in Nobles County, Minnesota, United States.
The population was 260 at the 2000 census.
========,2,Geography.
According to the United States Census Bureau, the township has a total area of 36.0 square miles (93.2 km²), all of it land.
The main geographic features of Little Rock Township are the Little Rock River and the Little Rock Creek.
